# .doc-governance/ignore — copy to .doc-governance/ignore to activate.
#
# One glob per line. Syntax:
#   *   matches within a single path segment (not across /)
#   **  matches across segments
#   /   trailing slash means "this directory and everything under it"
#   #   comment (line-based)
#
# No negation, no [charclass], no ?. Matches are checked against POSIX
# repo-relative paths. Applies to BOTH .md docs (they drop out of the map)
# AND code files (their changes stop triggering warnings).
#
# Typical noise sources — uncomment the ones that apply.

# Third-party skill/plugin drops already excluded by default, but keep here
# if you drop them at non-standard paths:
# vendor-skills/**
# .assistant/skills/**

# Ephemeral planning docs you don't want mapped:
# docs/plans/**
# Task*.md
# NOTES-*.md

# Auto-generated docs that regenerate on every build:
# docs/api/generated/**
# docs/openapi.md
